  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Provided informed consent

          2. Age 18 or older

          3. History of hyperoxaluria secondary to a known underlying enteric disorder associated
             with malabsorption (e.g., bariatric surgery, Crohn's disease, short bowel syndrome, or
             other malabsorption syndrome)

          4. Urinary Oxalate ≥50 mg/24h

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Acute renal failure or glomerular filtration rate &lt;30 mL/min/1.73 m2

          2. Unable or unwilling to discontinue Vitamin C supplementation
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
